## Plugins

### [gatsby-plugin-nprogress](https://www.gatsbyjs.org/packages/gatsby-plugin-nprogress/?=nprog).

### Customizing html.js

Gatsby uses a React component to server render the <head> and other parts of the HTML outside of the core Gatsby application.

Most sites should use the default html.js shipped with Gatsby. But if you need to customize your siteâ€™s html.js, copy the default one into your source tree by running:

```
cp .cache/default-html.js src/html.js
```
